ith%20external%20affairs%20minister%20S.%20Jaishankar%2C%20who%20assured%20continued%20humanitarian%20support%20to%20the%20country%20from%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20decision%20to%20engage%20with%20the%20Assad%20government%20comes%20close%20on%20the%20heels%20of%20Syria%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aljazeera.com%2Fnews%2F2023%2F5%2F7%2Farab-league-agrees-to-bring-syria-back-into-its-fold%5C%22%3Eregaining%20its%20membership%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20Arab%20League%20in%20May%20this%20year.%20Its%20membership%20was%20revoked%20after%20al-Assad%20ordered%20a%20crackdown%20on%20pro-democracy%20protesters%20during%20the%20so-called%20Arab%20Spring%20in%20March%202011%2C%20which%20spiralled%20into%20a%20civil%20war%20that%20has%20killed%20nearly%20hundreds%20of%20thousands%20and%20displaced%20millions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20conflict%2C%20India%20did%20not%20criticise%20the%20government%20and%20remained%20aligned%20with%20al-Assad.%20New%20Delhi%20also%20continued%20economic%20involvement%20in%20Syria.%20India%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.icwa.in%2Fshow_content.php%3Flang%3D1%26level%3D3%26ls_id%3D2387%26lid%3D1787%26kval%3Dsyria%5C%22%3Eopposed%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20external%20intervention%20or%20imposed%20solutions%20to%20the%20conflict%20and%20instead%20proposed%20a%20%E2%80%9CSyria-led%20solution%20in%20Syria%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Funsc-watch-as-russia-us-clash-over-syria-cross-border-aid-india-aligns-with-moscow%5C%22%3EAs%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20has%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20consistent%20support%20for%20the%20al-Assad%20regime%20is%20principally%20based%20on%20its%20assessment%20that%20he%20had%20been%20an%20%E2%80%9Ceffective%20bulwark%20against%20the%20spread%20of%20the%20terror%20group%20ISIS%2C%20not%20only%20in%20West%20Asia%20but%20also%20in%20the%20larger%20region%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689261364000%2