ary%20tightening%20has%20caused%20mortgages%20to%20shoot%20up%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fcommodities%2Fmortgage-rise-housing-labor-market-federal-reserve-interest-monetary-policy-2023-7%3Futm_medium%3Dingest%26utm_source%3Dmarkets%5C%22%3Ean%20eight-month%20high%20of%207.22%25%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%93%20which%20should%2C%20in%20theory%2C%20cause%20home%20prices%20to%20decline.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20this%20hasn't%20held%20true.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fcommodities%2Fhousing-market-explained-mortgage-rates-fed-inventory-home-prices-house-2023-6%5C%22%3EWe%20explained%20last%20week%20how%20prices%20have%20remained%20resilient%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20face%20of%20high%20borrowing%20costs%2C%20deterring%20new%20buyers%20from%20purchasing%20and%20new%20sellers%20from%20listing.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAllianz%20thinks%20the%20worst%20is%20over%20for%20the%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20US%20housing%20market%20has%20been%20in%20a%20downturn%20over%20the%20last%20two%20years%20but%20it%20seems%20to%20have%20reached%20its%20end%2C%26quot%3B%20economists%20at%20the%20German%20insurance-to-asset%20management%20behemoth%20led%20by%20Ludovic%20Subran%20wrote%20in%20a%20recent%20research%20note.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAccording%20to%20the%20national%20accounts%2C%20private%20residential%20investment%20slumped%20more%20than%2020%25%20between%20Q1%202021%20and%20Q1%202023.%20However%2C%20private%20housing%20starts%20jumped%20in%20May%20as%20homebuilder%20confidence%20is%20rapidly%20improving%2C%26quot%3B%20they%20added.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20key%20issue%20in%20the%20current%20market%20is%20the%20shortage%20of%20supply%20%E2%80%93%20there%20are%20simply%20not%20enough%20homes%20on%20the%20market.%20A%20pick-up%20in%20construction%20would%20widen%20the%20available%20inventory%20and%20bridge%20the%20affordability%20gap%20for%20buyers%2C%20as%20homebuilders%20can%2