t%20employees%20spoke%20to%20Insider%20about%20their%20experiences%20working%20at%20the%20magazine.%20Despite%20changes%2C%20some%20remain%20unsatisfied%20with%20the%20company.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20June%2028%2C%202020%2C%20an%20anonymous%20group%20of%20women%20under%20the%20name%20of%20Black%20Females%20Anonymous%20published%20a%20damning%20public%20letter%20that%20shook%20the%20core%20of%20Essence%20Magazine%2C%20the%20leading%20publication%20for%20Black%20women%20in%20America.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Essence%20brand%20promise%20is%20fraudulent%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20essay%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmedium.com%2F%40blackfemaleanonymous2020%2Fthe-truth-about-essence-532152b08051%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epublished%20on%20Medium%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20claimed.%20%26quot%3BThe%20once%20exalted%20media%20brand%20dedicated%20to%20Black%20women%20has%20been%20hijacked%20by%20cultural%20and%20corporate%20greed%20and%20an%20unhinged%20abuse%20of%20power.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20letter%20alleged%20an%20%26quot%3Bextremely%20unhealthy%20work%20culture%26quot%3B%20rife%20with%20%26quot%3Bpay%20inequity%2C%20sexual%20harassment%2C%20corporate%20bullying%2C%20intimidation%2C%20colorism%20and%20classism%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20one%20that%20began%20when%20Richelieu%20Dennis%2C%20the%20beauty%20mogul%20behind%20SheaMoisture%2C%20bought%20the%20publication%20in%202018.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20letter%20hit%20the%20internet%2C%20Dennis%20and%20the%20rest%20of%20Essence's%20leadership%20scrambled%20to%20deal%20with%20the%20implosion.%20In%20a%20public%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.essence.com%2Fbusiness%2Fessence-official-statement-black-womens-anonymous%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estatement%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Essence%20denied%20the%20allegations%2C%20calling%20them%20%26quot%3Bmischaracterizations%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bunfounded%20attempts%20to%20discredit%20our%20brand%20and%20assassinate%20personal%20character.%26quot%3B%20It%20also%20hired%20two%20law%20firms%20to%20investigate%3B%20their%20independent%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.essence.com%2Fbusiness%2Fstatement-workplace-culture-essence-magazine%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereviews%3C%2Fa%3E%20could%20not%20substantiate%20claims%20made%20in%20the%20letter%2C%20including%20those%20of%20bullying%2C%20harassment%2C%20or%20discrimination.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20some%20employees%20say%20they%20witnessed%20management%20become%20increasingly%20defensive.%20The%20company%20held%20town%20hall%20meetings%20over%20Zoom%20where%20they%20encouraged%20people%20to%20speak%20up%20about%20their%20concerns.%20Only%20by%20airing%20out%20these%20concerns%2C%20they%20said%2C%20could%20they%20make%20the%20workplace%20better.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20some%20former%20employees%20who%20attended%20the%20meetings%20said%20the%20sentiment%20didn't%20feel%20sincere.%20Instead%2C%20they%20believed%20leadership%20became%20obsessed%20with%20sniffing%20out%20who%20wrote%20the%20letter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20was%20a%20critical%20turning%20point%20in%20establishing%20trust%20with%20employees%20again%2C%20and%20assuring%20us%20that%20our%20work%20matters%20here%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20former%20employee%20present%20at%20the%20meeting%20told%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BBut%20in%20the%20moment%20we%20were%20made%20to%20feel%20replaceable.%20It%20was%20a%20turning%20point%20where%20a%20lot%20of%20folks%20checked%20out.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERather%20than%20listen%20and%20take%20accountability%2C%20ex-employees%20said%20they%20felt%20like%20leadership%20tried%20to%20undermine%20their%20voices%20and%20their%20experiences%2C%20just%20as%20had%20been%20expressed%20in%20the%20open%20letter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEssence%20is%20the%20most%20deceptive%20Black%20media%20company%20in%20America.%20Why%3F%20Essence%20aggressively%20monetizes%20%23BlackGirlMagic%20but%20the%20company%20does%20not%20internally%20practice%20%23BlackGirlMagic%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20letter%20read.%20%26quot%3BThe%20company's%20longstanding%20pattern%20of%20gross%20mistreatment%20and%20abuse%20of%20its%20Black%20female%20employees%20is%20the%20biggest%20open%20secret%20in%20the%20media%20business.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInsider%20spoke%20with%2020%20former%20and%20current%20employees%2C%20ranging%20across%20titles%20and%20departments%2C%20about%20their%20experiences%20working%20at%20Essence.%20Five%20former%20employees%20were%20still%20at%20the%20magazine%20in%202022%20or%202023%3B%20an%20additional%20nine%20worked%20at%20Essence%20during%20the%20time%20the%20letter%20was%20published%20in%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20employees%20who%20were%20at%20Essence%20in%202020%20say%20they%20experienced%20or%20witnessed%20a%20%26quot%3Bhellish%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bdehumanizing%26quot%3B%20culture%20with%20a%20rigidly%20top-down%20hierarchy%2C%20compensation%20they%20were%20not%20happy%20with%2C%20and%20mismanagement%20%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%94%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eissues%20that%20current%20and%20recent%20employees%20say%20haven't%20entirely%20gone%20away%20in%20the%20three%20years%20since%20the%20letter%20was%20published.%20Most%20of%20the%20sources%20requested%20anonymity%20out%20of%20fear%20of%20retaliation%20and%20to%20protect%20their%20careers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEssence%20is%20a%20dream%20place%20%E2%80%94%20'Black%20girl%20magic'%20%E2%80%94%20but%20it's%20a%20known%20thing%20inside%2C%20and%20it's%20leaking%20outside%2C%20that%20it's%20more%20like%20'Black%20girl%20tragic%2C'%26quot%3B%20one%20former%20employee%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEssence%20and%20Group%20Black%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20multiple%20requests%20for%20comment%20from%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EEssence%20under%20Time%20Inc.%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEssence%20Magazine%20was%20first%20published%20in%201970%20at%20a%20time%20when%20Black%20business%20and%20civil%20rights%20leaders%20called%20for%20greater%20self-determination%20and%20empowerment.%20The%20magazine%20was%20the%20brainchild%20of%20a%20group%20of%20four%20Black%20businessmen%20who%20identified%20a%20lack%20of%20publications%20for%20Black%20women%20in%20America.%20It%20was%20meant%20to%20be%20a%20%26quot%3Blifestyle%20magazine%20directed%20at%20upscale%20African%20American%20women.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETheir%20vision%20was%20soon%20realized.%20With%20an%20initial%20circulation%20of%20only%20around%2050%2C000%20copies%20per%20month%2C%20the%20publication's%20readership%20grew%20by%20a%20staggering%2017-fold%20within%20two%20decades.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnder%20the%20helm%20of%20Susan%20Taylor%2C%20the%20publication's%20long%20beloved%20editor-in-chief%20from%201981%20to%202000%2C%20Essence's%20monthly%20readership%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehistorymakers.org%2Fbiography%2Fsusan-l-taylor%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esurpassed%3C%2Fa%3E%205%20million%20people%2C%20making%20the%20magazine%20a%20household%20name%20in%20Black%20communities%20across%20America.%20Taylor%20was%20also%20responsible%20for%20launching%20Essence%20Festival%2C%20an%20annual%20event%20that%20would%20become%20the%20company's%20biggest%20revenue%20generator%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Farticles%2Ftime-inc-looks-to-sell-majority-stake-in-essence-1500911326%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eeventually%20even%20overshadowing%3C%2Fa%3E%20what%20the%20magazine%20itself%20brought%20in%2C%20and%20turning%20the%20Essence%20brand%20into%20a%20cultural%20behemoth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20the%20magazine%20has%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.essence.com%2Fabout%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emonthly%20circulation%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20over%201%20million%20copies%2C%20competing%20with%20the%20likes%20of%20Vogue%20and%20Elle.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20things%20shifted%20in%202000%2C%20when%20Time%20Inc.%20%E2%80%94%20which%20also%20owned%20publications%20like%20Sports%20Illustrated%2C%20Fortune%2C%20and%20People%20%E2%80%94%20purchased%2049%25%20of%20Essence%20Communications%2C%20then%20later%20bought%20the%20remaining%2051%25%20in%202005.%20Essence%20went%20from%20one%20of%20the%20few%20Black-owned%20magazines%20in%20the%20country%20to%20another%20publication%20under%20widespread%20ownership.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223696%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20general%20view%20of%20magazine%20covers%20on%20display%20at%20the%20Celebration%20of%20ABC's%20TGIT%20Line-up%20presented%20by%20Toyota%20and%20co-hosted%20by%20ABC%20and%20Time%20Inc.'s%20Entertainment%20Weekly%2C%20Essence%20and%20People%20at%20Gracias%20Madre%20on%20September%2026%2C%202015%20in%20West%20Hollywood%2C%20CA.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64a82ad18ed31300199e1524%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222772%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECovers%20of%20Essence%20and%20Entertainment%20Weekly%2C%20both%20magazines%20under%20Time%20Inc.%20in%202015.%3Cp%3EJason%20Kempin%2FGetty%20Images%20for%20Entertainment%20Weekly%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20shift%20to%20a%20white-%20and%20male-dominated%20parent%20company%20left%20some%20employees%20feeling%20like%20Essence%20operated%20under%20%26quot%3Bstepchild%20status%26quot%3B%20under%20Time%20Inc.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20employee%20at%20the%20time%20said%20that%20it%20felt%20like%20Time%20Inc.%20%26quot%3Bwasn't%20invested%20in%20Essence%20at%20all.%26quot%3B%20People%20struggled%20with%20budgets%2C%20creating%20a%20%26quot%3Bbootstrapping%26quot%3B%20environment.%20The%20move%20to%20a%20multi-billion%20dollar%20media%20conglomerate%20had%20made%20some%20employees%20hope%20Essence%20would%20be%20given%20ample%20resources%3B%20instead%2C%20they%20seemed%20to%20operate%20from%20a%20scarcity%20mentality.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAll%20of%20the%20teams%20always%20moved%20as%20if%20there%20was%20extreme%20limitation%2C%20like%2C%20'we%20can't%20do%20this%20photoshoot%3B%20we%20don't%20have%20enough%20money%2C'%26quot%3B%20a%20former%20employee%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202013%2C%20then-president%20of%20Essence%20Communications%20Michelle%20Ebanks%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2013%2F07%2F24%2Fbusiness%2Fmedia%2Fawaiting-another-top-editor-essence-faces-identity-questions.html%3Fsmid%3Dnytcore-android-share%5C%22%20data-stringify-link%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2013%2F07%2F24%2Fbusiness%2Fmedia%2Fawaiting-another-top-editor-essence-faces-identity-questions.html%3Fsmid%3Dnytcore-android-share%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%20data-sk%3D%5C%22tooltip_parent%5C%22%3Etold%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0The%20New%20York%20Times%20she%20understood%20why%20some%20readers%20were%20concerned%20about%20Time%20Inc.'s%20influence%20on%20the%20magazine%2C%20but%20insisted%20that%20Essence%20enjoys%20%26quot%3Bjournalistic%20independence%26quot%3B%20under%20their%20parent%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ERich%20Dennis%20enters%20the%20scene%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202017%2C%20the%20Meredith%20Corporation%20announced%20it%20would%20purchase%20Time%20Inc.%20for%20%242.8%20billion%2C%20acquiring%20all%20the%20publication's%20assets%2C%20including%20Essence%20Magazine.%20The%20company%20had%20struggled%20with%20plummeting%20print%20advertising%20revenue%2C%20like%20much%20of%20the%20publishing%20industry.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAround%20that%20time%2C%20Richelieu%20Dennis%20came%20across%20a%20Wall%20Street%20Journal%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Farticles%2Ftime-inc-looks-to-sell-majority-stake-in-essence-1500911326%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Earticle%3C%2Fa%3E%20about%20how%20Time%20Inc.%20was%20looking%20to%20sell%20its%20majority%20stake%20in%20Essence.%20Dennis%20had%20made%20his%20name%20and%20fortune%20as%20the%20founder%20of%20Sundial%20Brands%2C%20a%20beauty%20company%20that%20focuses%20on%20products%20for%20Black%20women%2C%20including%20SheaMoisture%20and%20Nubian%20Heritage.%20He%20had%20no%20prior%20experience%20in%20the%20media%20industry%2C%20but%20felt%20strongly%20about%20serving%20the%20Black%20community.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20January%202018%2C%20Dennis%20bought%20Essence%20from%20Time%20Inc.%20for%20an%20undisclosed%20amount.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20stars%20aligned%2C%26quot%3B%20Dennis%20told%20NNPA%20Newswire%20soon%20after%20the%20purchase.%20%26quot%3BWe%20started%20to%20think%20about%20the%20implications%20of%20what%20this%20would%20mean%20if%20Essence%20were%20truly%20brought%20back%20into%20the%20community.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223328%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Richelieu%20Dennis%20speaks%20onstage%20during%20the%202023%20ESSENCE%20Ventures%20Media%20Upfronts%20at%20The%20Fillmore%20New%20Orleans%20on%20June%2029%2C%202023%20in%20New%20Orleans%2C%20Louisiana.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64a8438f6d7e02001af8790e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222496%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERichelieu%20Dennis%20at%20the%202023%20Essence%20Ventures%20Media%20Upfronts%20on%20June%2029%2C%202023.%3Cp%3EArturo%20Holmes%2FGetty%20Images%20for%20ESSENCE%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EReaders%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.okayafrica.com%2Frichelieu-dennis-shea-moisture-acquires-essence-magazine%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecelebrated%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20magazine%20was%20Black-owned%20again.%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20so%20so%20so%20so%20so%20important%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20reader%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2F_TARYNitUP%2Fstatus%2F948637539006664704%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etweeted%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BWe%20need%20room%20for%20this%20celebration%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FLuvvie%2Fstatus%2F948682340632588288%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eanother%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen-president%20of%20Essence%20Communications%20Michelle%20Ebanks%2C%20who%20stayed%20through%20the%20acquisition%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Farticles%2Ftime-inc-sells-essence-to-company-formed-by-co-founder-of-sundial-brands-1515013472%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20this%20was%20a%20chance%20for%20the%20publication%20to%20grow%3A%20%26quot%3BThis%20means%20we%20can%20realize%20our%20extraordinary%20potential.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDennis%20had%20brought%20back%20hope.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBorn%20in%20Liberia%20in%201969%20to%20a%20family%20of%20entrepreneurs%2C%20Dennis%20came%20to%20America%20to%20attend%20Babson%20College%2C%20a%20business%20school%20whose%20gilded%20roster%20of%20alumni%20includes%20execs%20from%20The%20Home%20Depot%2C%20PepsiCo%2C%20and%20Accenture.%20Unable%20to%20return%20home%20because%20of%20a%20civil%20war%2C%20Dennis%20started%20Sundial%20Brands%20in%20his%20tiny%20Queens%20apartment%2C%20making%20soaps%20and%20lotions%20from%20shea%20butter%20and%20essential%20oils%20in%20his%20bathtub.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%20its%20modest%20beginnings%2C%20Sundial%20raked%20in%20around%20%24300%20million%20in%20revenue%20in%202017%2C%20and%20ultimately%20sold%20to%20Unilever%20for%20an%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.forbes.com%2Fsites%2Felanagross%2F2020%2F07%2F02%2Fessence-ceo-richelieu-dennis-resigns-following-allegations-of-a-toxic-workplace-culture%2F%3Fsh%3D7cde6f6622c5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eestimated%3C%2Fa%3E%20%241.6%20billion%20later%20that%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20founder%20escaped%20war%2C%20created%20a%20top%20skin%20care%20brand%2C%20and%20launched%20a%20%24100%20million%20fund%20for%20Black%20women%20entrepreneurs%2C%26quot%3B%20Inc.%20Magazine%20wrote%20of%20Dennis'%20accomplishments%20in%202019.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223917%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Richelieu%20Dennis%20(Founder%2C%20SheaMoisture)%20attends%20Variety's%20Power%20of%20Women%20presented%20by%20Lifetime%20at%20Cipriani%20Midtown%20on%20April%205%2C%202019%20in%20New%20York%20City%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64a82b866d7e02001af8723e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222611%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERichelieu%20Dennis%20at%20Variety%20Magazine's%20Power%20of%20Women%20event%20in%202019.%3Cp%3EMargarita%20Corporan%2FVariety%2FPenske%20Media%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20of%20Sundial's%20loyal%20customers%20lambasted%20the%20Unilever%20sale%20as%20a%20betrayal%20of%20its%20founding%20mission%20to%20support%20Black%20women.%20But%20Dennis%20said%20that%20these%20decisions%20were%20ways%20to%20reinvest%20in%20the%20Black%20community%20%E2%80%94%20a%20sentiment%20he%20echoed%20when%20he%20bought%20Essence%20in%202018.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20we're%20doing%20with%20Essence%20is%20not%20very%20different%20from%20what%20we've%20done%20with%20Sundial%2C%26quot%3B%20Dennis%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.forbes.com%2Fsites%2Fmaddieberg%2F2018%2F09%2F21%2Fthese-black-entrepreneurs-went-from-selling-soap-on-harlem-streets-to-a-850-million-fortune%2F%3Fsh%3D7d24f53d4b14%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etold%3C%2Fa%3E%20Forbes%20in%202018%20when%20he%20bought%20the%20magazine.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20that%20is%20to%20serve%20Black%20women%20deeply%2C%20to%20serve%20women%20of%20color%20in%20a%20way%20that%20no%20one%20else%20has%20thought%20about.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEssence%20Magazine%20was%20Dennis'%20first%20foray%20into%20the%20media%20world%2C%20and%20was%20just%20the%20first%20in%20a%20string%20of%20acquisition