quot%3B%20one%20former%20employee%20recalled%20of%20the%20transition.%20%26quot%3BSo%20it%20was%20a%20moment%20of%20pride%20%E2%80%94%20for%20all%20of%20us.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20reality%20of%20Essence%20under%20Dennis'%20early%20leadership%2C%20however%2C%20did%20not%20meet%20some%20staffers'%20high%20expectations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEssence%20was%20once%20again%20a%20Black-owned%20company%20and%2C%20as%20executives%20regularly%20liked%20to%20remind%20us%2C%20we%20were%20family.%20As%20we%20all%20know%2C%20however%2C%20a%20company%20is%20not%20your%20family.%20It%20is%20business%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20former%20editor%20at%20the%20magazine%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fsydneymscott%2Fstatus%2F1277735205705584640%2Fphoto%2F1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20a%20tweet%20around%20the%20time%20of%20the%20anonymous%20letter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ECrumbling%20morale%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEssence%20had%20suffered%20from%20a%20lack%20of%20resources%20under%20Time%20Inc.%2C%20and%20Dennis%20and%20his%20leadership%20team%20were%20tasked%20with%20righting%20a%20sinking%20ship.%20But%20the%20new%20management%20faced%20immediate%20obstacles%20it%20struggled%20to%20overcome%2C%20leaving%20some%20employees%20questioning%20their%20ability%20to%20run%20a%20media%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20sale%20to%20Dennis%20in%202018%2C%20management%20failed%20to%20construct%20a%20stable%20infrastructure%2C%20eight%20current%20and%20former%20employees%20told%20Insider.%20There%20were%20no%20annual%20reviews%20or%20promotion%20outlines%2C%20leaving%20ambitious%20employees%20feeling%20stuck%20and%20frustrated.%20Even%20those%20with%20supportive%20managers%20who%20championed%20their%20work%20struggled%20to%20advance%20in%20the%20company%2C%20since%20the%20buck%20stopped%20at%20the%20C-suite%2C%20employees%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnly%20one%20of%20the%2011%20sources%20Insider%20spoke%20with%20who%20were%20there%20at%20the%20time%20received%20raises%20in%20the%20first%20few%20years%20of%20Dennis'%20ownership%2C%20they%20say.%20Many%20of%20those%20staff%20members%20said%20they%20had%20to%20juggle%20multiple%20responsibilities%20outside%20of%20their%20original%20job%20descriptions%20and%20felt%20it%20only%20exacerbated%20the%20pain%20of%20not%20receiving%20a%20raise%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20as%20Essence%20sought%20to%20ramp%20up%20its%20digital%20presence.%20Dennis%20had%20grand%20visions%20for%20Essence%20and%20wanted%20to%20run%20the%20magazine%20as%20a%20multi-faceted%20%26quot%3Bstartup%2C%26quot%3B%20insiders%20recalled%20him%20saying.%20The%20industry-wide%20shift%20from%20print%20to%20digital%20meant%20a%20demand%20for%20more%20stories%2C%20more%20quickly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EReporters%20at%20Essence%20in%20the%20first%20few%20years%20under%20Dennis'%20leadership%20said%20they%20had%20to%20write%20four%20to%20five%20stories%20per%20day%20for%20the%20website%2C%20while%20also%20working%20on%20stories%20for%20the%20print%20magazine.%20Some%20editorial%20staff%20also%20took%20on%20new%20podcasts%20and%20visual%20projects%2C%20but%20weren't%20compensated%20for%20the%20extra%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20had%20basically%20taken%20a%20pay%20cut%20from%20them%20with%20the%20additional%20responsibilities%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20former%20employee%20who%20was%20there%20in%202018%20to%202020%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20was%20told%20to%20take%20it%20or%20leave%20it.%20Others%20didn't%20get%20extra%20for%20their%20additional%20contributions%2C%20either%2C%20so%20I%20felt%20like%20I%20couldn't%20complain%20about%20it.%20But%20I%20did%20feel%20insulted.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20women%20said%20the%20stressful%20work%20culture%20started%20to%20affect%20their%20mental%20and%20physical%20health.%20They%20relied%20on%20their%20%26quot%3Bsisterhood%26quot%3B%20to%20get%20through%20the%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20culture%20is%20very%20much%20a%20community%20%E2%80%94%20a%20team%20that%20translates%20and%20speaks%20well%20with%20each%20other%2C%26quot%3B%20Sandra%20Okerulu%2C%20a%20freelancer%20who%20worked%20with%20Essence%20in%202018%2C%20said%20of%20the%20magazine's%20employees.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20clear%20they%20believe%20in%20the%20project.%20This%20is%20theirs.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20when%20staff%20tried%20to%20voice%20their%20frustrations%20to%20higher-ups%2C%20some%20say%20they%20were%20met%20with%20apathy.%20At%20multiple%20town%20hall%20meetings%20from%202018%20to%202020%2C%20Michelle%20Ebanks%2C%20then-CEO%20of%20Essence%20Communications%2C%20said%20if%20they%20didn't%20like%20what%20they%20were%20being%20paid%2C%20they%20could%20leave%20out%20the%20door%2C%20several%20former%20employees%20told%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20the%20end%20of%202018%2C%20less%20than%20a%20year%20into%20Dennis'%20reign%2C%20morale%20began%20to%20crumble.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20kind%20of%20hope%20that%20Essence%20is%20one%20of%20those%20places%20that%20won't%20treat%20you%20like%20a%20cog%20in%20the%20wheel%2C%20but%20that%20wasn't%20the%20case%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20former%20employee%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20new%20regime%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20of%20the%20problems%20at%20Essence%20predated%20Dennis'%20purchase%2C%20four%20former%20employees%20said%2C%20but%20the%20real%20root%20of%20the%20persisting%20issues%20lay%20in%20the%20upper%20echelons%20of%20the%20magazine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20cultural%20rot%20was%20from%20the%20top%20down%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20former%20employee%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20October%202018%2C%20Dennis%20brought%20in%20Moana%20Luu%2C%20a%20self-described%20multihyphenate%20from%20Martinique%2C%20to%20shore%20up%20Essence%20as%20its%20chief%20content%20and%20creative%20officer.%20Statuesque%20with%20a%20cosmopolitan%20flair%2C%20Luu%20held%20a%20patchwork%20of%20jobs%20in%20beauty%2C%20media%2C%20and%20design%20before%20joining%20Essence.%20She%20was%20a%20TV%20producer%20and%20host%20for%20a%20local%20Marticinian%20pageant%20show%2C%20creative%20director%20for%20a%20French%20hair%20care%20company%2C%20and%20chief%20creative%20officer%20for%20a%20studio%20based%20in%20France%20called%20Trace%20Media%2C%20per%20her%20LinkedIn%20profile.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELuu%2C%20who%20lived%20in%20Paris%20and%20the%20Philippines%20before%20moving%20to%20America%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.forbes.com%2Fsites%2Fdaniellehughes%2F2019%2F05%2F29%2Fconversations-from-the-c-suite-moana-luu-is-challenging-the-status-quo-as-content-and-creative-director-of-essence-magazine%2F%3Fsh%3D55784de465fe%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewas%20tasked%20with%20globalizing%20the%20reach%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20Essence.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20multiple%20employees%20questioned%20her%20ability%20to%20run%20a%20magazine%20with%20a%20storied%20heritage%20like%20Essence.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223076%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Essence%20CEO%20Michelle%20Ebanks%2C%20Essence%20Ventures%20Founder%20%26amp%3B%20Chairman%20Richelieu%20Dennis%2C%20and%20Essence%20Chief%20Content%20%26amp%3B%20Creative%20Officer%20Moana%20Luu%20pose%20onstage%20during%20the%202020%2013th%20Annual%20ESSENCE%20Black%20Women%20in%20Hollywood%20Luncheon%20at%20Beverly%20Wilshire%2C%20A%20Four%20Seasons%20Hotel%20on%20February%2006%2C%202020%20in%20Beverly%20Hills%2C%20California.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64a82cc08ed31300199e157f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222307%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EEssence%20CEO%20Michelle%20Ebanks%2C%20Richelieu%20Dennis%2C%20and%20Essence%20chief%20content%20%26amp%3B%20creative%20officer%20Moana%20Luu%20at%20the%202020%2013th%20Annual%20ESSENCE%20Black%20Women%20in%20Hollywood%20luncheon.%3Cp%3ERich%20Polk%2FGetty%20Images%20for%20Essence%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20letter%2C%20Luu%20was%20accused%20of%20%26quot%3Bworkplace%20bullying%2C%20flamboyant%20overspending%2C%20and%20lack%20of%20leadership%20on%20production%20budgets%20and%20deadlines.%26quot%3B%20Multiple%20sources%20told%20Insider%20they%20had%20similar%20experiences%20with%20Luu%2C%20with%20some%20sources%20feeling%20like%20she%20caused%20issues%20of%20the%20magazine%20to%20be%20late%20to%20press%20because%20of%20last-minute%20changes%2C%20or%20shifting%20deadlines.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20sources%20felt%20that%20both%20Dennis%20and%20Luu%20lacked%20%26quot%3Bdeep%20knowledge%26quot%3B%20of%20the%20publishing%20industry%2C%20leading%20to%20a%20lot%20of%20%26quot%3Bmisunderstanding%20about%20the%20time%20and%20effort%20needed%20to%20publish%20a%20monthly%20magazine%2C%26quot%3B%20as%20one%20former%20employee%20put%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20employees%20who%20worked%20with%20Luu%20felt%20she%20also%20fostered%20a%20%26quot%3Bmean%20girl%26quot%3B%20workplace.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BShe%20pretty%20much%20came%20in%20trying%20to%20be%20the%20Black%20version%20of%20'Devil%20Wears%20Prada%2C'%26quot%3B%20a%20former%20editor%20said.%20Another%20former%20employee%20felt%20Luu%20held%20%26quot%3Bvery%20little%20respect%26quot%3B%20for%20the%20women%20who%20worked%20at%20Essence.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELuu%20commented%20on%20people's%20weight%20and%20appearance%2C%20six%20sources%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20an%20editor%20with%20a%20curvier%20body%20type%20pitched%20an%20idea%20for%20a%20video%2C%20Luu%20reportedly%20responded%2C%20%26quot%3BYou%20on%20camera%3F%20No%20no%20no%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20editor%20told%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BShe%20told%20me%20that%20she%20needed%20someone%20beautiful%20with%20a%20lot%20of%20social%20media%20numbers%2C%20not%20me%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20editor%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20just%20stopped%20after%20that.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20former%20employee%20who%20witnessed%20the%20interaction%20corroborated%20the%20incident.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20big%20part%20of%20Essence's%20platform%20has%20been%20showcasing%20the%20varied%20beauty%20of%20Black%20women%3A%20all%20shapes%20and%20sizes%2C%20all%20shades%2C%20all%20hair%20textures%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20former%20longtime%20editor%20at%20the%20magazine%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBut%20when%20Moana%20came%20on%20board%2C%20she%20was%20only%20interested%20in%20a%20certain%20aesthetic%2C%20and%20she%20wanted%20that%20certain%20aesthetic%20to%20be%20the%20face%20of%20the%20brand%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20editor%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20Luu's%20tenure%2C%20Essence%20did%20promote%20on-screen%20personalities%20including%20Danielle%20Young%2C%20who%20used%20the%20platform%20to%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.essence.com%2Fvideos%2Fwhat-is-body-positivity%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20champion%3C%2Fa%3E%20body%20positivity%20and%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.essence.com%2Fvideos%2Fthe-overexplainer-we-are-only-just-now-stopping-black-hair-discrimination%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Espeak%20out%20against%3C%2Fa%3E%20texturism.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20investigation%20into%20the%20allegations%20made%20in%20the%20Medium%20post%20in%202020%20%26quot%3Bdid%20not%20find%20that%20Ms.%20Luu%20treated%20anyone%20differently%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.essence.com%2Fbusiness%2Fstatement-workplace-culture-essence-magazine%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epublic%20statement%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20Essence.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20investigation%20also%20found%20that%20%26quot%3Bseveral%20witnesses%20reported%20hearing%20her%20make%20insensitive%20comments%26quot%3B%20and%20that%20some%20employees%20felt%20her%20management%20style%20was%20%26quot%3Bintimidating%20and%20brash.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELuu%20said%20she%20was%20%26quot%3Badamant%20that%20%5Bwas%5D%20not%20her%20intent%20to%20bully%20anyone%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20the%20investigation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20first%20two%20years%20of%20Dennis'%20ownership%2C%20top%20brass%20at%20Essence%20left%20the%20publication%2C%20including%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwwd.com%2Fbusiness-news%2Fmedia%2Fcosmopolitan-pulls-beauty-director-essence-1203548766%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eglobal%20beauty%20director%20Julee%20Wilson%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theatlantic.com%2Fpress-releases%2Farchive%2F2021%2F01%2Fcandace-montgomery-gm-atlanticlive-first-look-2021-plans%2F617702%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Evice%20president%20Candace%20Montgomery%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20who%20was%20instrumental%20in%20growing%20Essence's%20events.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAround%20the%20same%20time%2C%20other%20employees%20followed%20suit.%20According%20to%20five%20former%20employees%2C%20some%20staffers%20did%20not%20feel%20aligned%20with%20Luu's%20mission%20of%20globalizing%20a%20publication%20that%20was%20founded%20for%20Black%20American%20women%20and%20felt%20the%20new%20leadership%20was%20sidelining%20the%20demographic%20they%20were%20originally%20meant%20to%20uplift.%20(These%20sources%20could%20not%20speak%20specifically%20to%20why%20Wilson%20or%20Montgomery%20chose%20to%20leave).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELuu%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20requests%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EAllegations%20of%20nepotism%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDennis'%20hope%20to%20foster%20a%20%26quot%3Bfamily%26quot%3B%20at%20Essence%20played%20out%20in%20more%20ways%20than%20one.%20The%20new%20regime%20at%20Essence%20in%202018%20and%20its%20sister%20companies%20included%20multiple%20members%20of%20Dennis'%20own%20family%2C%20including%20his%20wife%20and%20two%20daughters.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20company's%20first%20several%20months%20under%20Dennis%2C%20there%20was%20no%20official%20human%20resources%20department%2C%20according%20to%2011%20former%20employees.%20Dennis'%20wife%2C%20Martha%2C%20became%20the%20de%20facto%20interim%20head%20of%20HR%2C%20nine%20former%20employees%20said.%20A%20401(k)%20document%20from%20November%202020%2C%20viewed%20by%20Insider%2C%20lists%20Martha%20Dennis%20as%20the%20contact%20person%2C%20alongside%20the%20address%20of%20Essence's%20office%20in%20Industry%20City%2C%20Brooklyn.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20Essence%20employees%20who%20spoke%20to%20Insider%20said%20they%20felt%20uncomfortable%20raising%20issues%20with%20the%20magazine%20owner's%20wife.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20I%20didn't%20have%20any%20complaints%2C%20it%20was%20because%20I%20didn't%20know%20who%20to%20go%20to%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20former%20employee%20said.%20%26quot%3BWith%20the%20owner's%20wife%20being%20in%20charge%20of%20HR%2C%20it%20didn't%20feel%20like%20a%20safe%20space%20to%20go%20to.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20their%20findings%2C%20the%20independent%20investigation%20claimed%20that%20there%20was%20%26quot%3Bno%20evidence%20to%20suggest%20that%20Ms.%20Dennis%20was%20appointed%20to%20lead%20HR%20or%20that%20she%20ever%20led%20HR%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20rather%20that%20she%20%26quot%3Bassisted%26quot%3B%20with%20HR%20matters.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDennis'%20daughters%2C%20Rechelle%20and%20Sophia%2C%20were%20given%20the%20reins%20to%20launch%20Essence%20Girls%20United%2C%20the%20Gen%20Z%20branch%20of%20the%20magazine.%20Rechelle%20was%20only%20a%20year%20out%20of%20college%20when%20she%20joined%20Essence%2C%20her%20LinkedIn%20shows.%20She%20also%20founded%20SheaGirl%2C%20a%20skincare%20company%20for%20teens%20under%20her%20father's%20company%20SheaMoisture%2C%20when%20she%20was%20a%20sophomore%20in%20college.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOutside%20of%20Essence%2C%20Dennis'%20sister%20Richelyna%20Hall%20was%20chief%20impact%20officer%20of%20New%20Voices%2C%20the%20organization%20Dennis%20founded%20to%20support%20women%20entrepreneurs%20of%20color%2C%20as%20recently%20as%202021.%20New%20Voices%20has%20hosted%20pitch%20competitions%20at%20EssenceFest%2C%20Essence%20magazine's%20annual%20festival%2C%20according%20to%20its%20website%2C%20and%20its%20portfolio%20companies%20%E2%80%94%20which%20it%20refers%20to%20as%20its%20%26quot%3Bfamily%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20have%20been%20featured%20on%20the%20magazine's%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Fp%2FCpWIm3VMWmC%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecover%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20in%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Fp%2FCoYhkkDOUKG%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewrite-ups%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20non-disclosure%20agreement%20that%20management%20asked%20employees%20to%20sign%20before%20a%20company%20event%20at%20the%20Dennis'%20Hamptons%20residence%20in%20the%20summer%20of%202019%20included%20language%20that%20prevents%20them%20from%20speaking%20about%20%26quot%3BDennis%2C%20Dennis'%20family%20members%20and%20children%2C%20friends%2C%20companies%2C%20business%20ventures%2C%20business%20associates%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20a%20copy%20Insider%20viewed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20types%20of%20agreements%20are%20a%20way%20for%20companies%20to%20control%20what%20people%20say%2C%20labor%20and%20employment%20lawyer%20Alan%20Lescht%20said.%20He%20added%20that%20it's%20not%20typical%20for%20NDAs%20to%20name%20specific%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20Essence%20staff%20bristled%20at%20the%20NDA.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20felt%20like%20it%20was%20%3Cem%3Etheir%20%3C%2Fem%3Efamily%2C%20but%20we%20weren't%20part%20of%20it.%20It%20definitely%20didn't%20feel%20like%20a%20family%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20former%20employee%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E'The%20Truth%20About%20Essence'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20June%2028%2C%202020%2C%20discontent%20within%20Essence%20had%20reached%20a%20fever%20pitch%2C%20culminating%20in%20the%20explosive%20Medium%20essay%20titled%20%26quot%3BThe%20Truth%20About%20Essence.%26quot%3B%20In%20addition%20to%20allegations%20of%20corporate%20bullying%20and%20an%20unhealthy%20work%20culture%2C%20the%20letter%20called%20for%20the%20resignation%20of%20Dennis%2C%20Ebanks%2C%20Luu%2C%20and%20chief%20operating%20officer%20Joy%20Collins%20Profet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EReaders%20rallied%20behind%20the%20anonymous%20group%20of%20writers%20in%20a%20petition%20that%20accompanied%20the%20essay.%20Several%20of%20those%20who%20signed%20the%20petition%20wrote%20that%20the%20content%20had%20deteriorated%20in%20the%20past%20decade%20and%20%26quot%3Bfails%20to%20speak%20to%20Black%20women.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20said%20they%20noticed%20that%20%26quot%3Bthe%20advertisements%20in%20the%20magazine%20contained%20fewer%20Black%20models%20of%20varying%20complexions%20and%20looked%20like%20something%20%5Bthey'd%5D%20see%20in%20Vogue%20or%20other%20similar%20magazines.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EReaders%20also%20decried%20the%20hypocrisy%20of%20a%20Black-owned%20business%20and%20claims%20of%20mistreating%20the%20Black%20women%20who%20make%20up%20the%20company.%20%26quot%3BA%20double%20slap%20in%20the%20face%20when%20it's%20done%20by%20our%20own%2C%26quot%3B%20someone%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEssence's%20management%20went%20into%20damage-control%20mode.%20A%20spokeswoman%20for%20the%20magazine%20denied%20that%20Martha%20Dennis%20was%20the%20head%20of%20human%20resources%2C%20saying%20that%20she%20had%20%26quot%3Badvised%20the%20company%20in%20its%20ongoing%20HR%20transition%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2020%2F07%2F02%2Fbusiness%2Fmedia%2Fessence-magazine-accusations.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20New%20York%20Times%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%20an%20internal%20response%20to%20employees%20viewed%20by%20Insider%2C%20management%20described%20HR%2C%20which%20they%20said%20they%20built%20from%20the%20%26quot%3Bground-up%2C%26quot%3B%20as%20having%20been%20%26quot%3Bsupported%20by%20a%20family%20executive%26quot%3B%20with%20experience%20in%20HR%20while%20they%20searched%20for%20a%20full-time%20lead.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDennis%2C%20Luu%2C%20and%20Ebanks%20stepped%20down%20from%20their%20positions%20or%20%26quot%3Bhad%20no%20role%20in%20day-to-day%20operations%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20spokeswoman%20told%20The%20New%20York%20Times.%20Collins%20Profet%20said%20she%20had%20previously%20notified%20Essence%20of%20her%20resignation%20in%202020%20to%20pursue%20another%20opportunity.%20Essence%20hired%20an%20interim%20CEO%2C%20Caroline%20Wanga%2C%20to%20help%20shore%20up%20the%20company.%20(Ebanks%2C%20Wanga%2C%20and%20Martha%20Dennis%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20requests%20for%20comment%20from%20Insider.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20town%20hall%20meetings%20management%20held%20following%20the%20letter%2C%20some%20Essence%20employees%20felt%20leadership%20didn't%20care%20to%20understand%20their%20employees'%20grievances%2C%20but%20rather%20positioned%20themselves%20as%20victims%20who%20had%20been%20%26quot%3Battacked.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDennis%20said%20that%20it%20had%20been%20a%20%26quot%3Bdifficult%20day%26quot%3B%20with%20%26quot%3Bour%20business%20being%20attacked%20in%20this%20way%20and%20our%20team%20members%20being%20attacked%20this%20way%2C%26quot%3B%20during%20a%20town%20hall%20meeting%20on%20June%2028%2C%202020%2C%20the%20same%20day%20the%20Medium%20post%20was%20published%2C%20according%20to%20a%20recording%20of%20the%20meeting%20that%20Insider%20reviewed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20successive%20town%20halls%2C%20employees%20said%20management%20continued%20to%20be%20%26quot%3Bvery%20dismissive%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bdisheartening.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20centuries%2C%20Black%20women's%20stories%20of%20oppression%20and%20mistreatment%20have%20been%20written%20off%2C%20and%20for%20Essence%20the%20brand%20to%20plainly%20state%20that%20fully%20denies%20accusations%20without%20any%20talk%20of%20investigation%20of%20the%20claims%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20always%20been%20what's%20done%20to%20us%20in%20history%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20employee%20said%20in%20a%20town%20hall%20meeting%20on%20June%2030%2C%20a%20recording%20of%20which%20Insider%20heard.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDennis%2C%20Wanga%2C%20and%20Martha%20Dennis%20defended%20leadership's%20efforts.%20In%20the%20June%2028%20meeting%2C%20Dennis%20said%20he%20believed%20they%20%26quot%3Bbrought%20real%20change%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20to%20change%20%26quot%3Ba%20culture%20that%20has%20evolved%20over%2050%20years%26quot%3B%20within%20two%20years%20was%20near%20impossible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20we%20really%20want%20to%20hear%20is%20an%20acknowledgement%2C%20an%20apology%20that%20says%2C%20'I'm%20sorry%20I%20let%20you%20down%2C'%26quot%3B%20an%20employee%20said%20in%20the%20June%2030%20town%20hall.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20doesn't%20take%20away%20from%20your%20greatness.%20It%20doesn't%20take%20away%20from%20your%20purpose.%20It%20doesn't%20take%20away%20from%20your%20position%20in%20this%20company%20and%20in%20this%20world.%20But%20it%20does%20signify%20to%20us%20you%20hear%20us%20and%20you%20see%20us%2C%20and%20that%20you%20see%20that%20we're%20hurting%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20employee%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFormer%20employees%20say%20they%20never%20received%20that%20acknowledgement%20or%20apology.%20Instead%2C%20leadership%20continued%20to%20prod%20and%20investigate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EGaslit%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEssence%20hired%20two%20white-shoe%20law%20firms%20to%20look%20into%20the%20essay's%20claims%20in%20July%202020.%20Employees%20said%20they%20received%20emails%2C%20sent%20to%20their%20work%20accounts%2C%20asking%20them%20for%20voluntary%20group%20or%20individual%20interviews.%20Some%20said%20they%20didn't%20feel%20comfortable%20speaking%20to%20the%20lawyers%20because%20they%20were%20afraid%20of%20retaliation.%20Others%20said%20they%20didn't%20receive%20any%20emails%20at%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20law%20firms%20ultimately%20concluded%20that%20the%20allegations%20lodged%20in%20the%20essay%20were%20unsubstantiated%2C%20including%20claims%20of%20bullying%2C%20nepotism%2C%20and%20discrimination.%20The%20results%20of%20the%20review%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.essence.com%2Fbusiness%2Fstatement-workplace-culture-essence-magazine%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epublished%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20a%20statement%20on%20Essence's%20website%2C%20also%20found%20that%20%26quot%3Bvarious%20issues%20contributing%20to%20work%20culture%20existed%20under%20prior%20ownership%2C%26quot%3B%20when%20Essence%20was%20under%20Time%20Inc.'s%20purview.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20report%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.essence.com%2Fbusiness%2Fthird-party-investigation-findings-harassment-allegations%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efound%3C%2Fa%3E%20allegations%20from%20the%20Medium%20post%20of%20sexual%20harassment%20to%20be%20unsubstantiated.%20The%20sources%20Insider%20spoke%20with%20said%20they%20had%20not%20witnessed%20or%20experienced%20inappropriate%20behavior%20of%20the%20kind%20alleged%20in%20the%20post.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20all%20employees%20supported%20the%20Medium%20post%20and%20the%20%23TakeBackEssence%20social%20media%20movement%20it%20catalyzed.%20Some%20felt%20the%20allegations%20could%20damage%20their%20livelihoods%2C%20and%20that%20the%20writers%20were%20disrespecting%20an%20institution%20they'd%20all%20worked%20so%20hard%20to%20uphold%20%E2%80%94%20illustrating%20the%20difficult%20position%20of%20being%20a%20Black%20woman%20in%20an%20industry%20where%20there%20are%20so%20few%20options%20available%20to%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20employees%20felt%20management's%20response%20and%20the%20investigation's%20findings%20to%20the%20essay%20dismissed%20their%20own%20lived%20experiences%20at%20Essence%20%E2%80%94%20even%20things%20they%20had%20seen%20with%20their%20own%20eyes%2C%20like%20Dennis'%20wife%20performing%20HR%20functions%20or%20Luu%20stepping%20back%20from%20the%20company%20following%20the%20Medium%20post.%20(Though%20recent%20employees%20said%20Luu%20no%20longer%20appears%20to%20be%20involved%20in%20the%20day-to-day%20operations%20at%20the%20magazine%2C%20she%20switched%20her%20title%20to%20%26quot%3Bglobal%20chief%20content%20and%20creative%20officer%26quot%3B%20at%20Essence%20Communications%20in%20September%202020%2C%20according%20to%20her%20LinkedIn%20and%20Instagram%20bio.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20place%20that%20%5Bmade%5D%20you%20feel%20gaslit%20at%20times%2C%20a%20place%20that%20creates%20confusion%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20former%20employee%20said.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20I%20lost%20my%20job%20in%202020%2C%20I%20was%20relieved%2C%20like%2C%20I%20don't%20have%20to%20feel%20like%20I'm%20in%20the%20'Twilight%20Zone'%20every%20day.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELeadership%20never%20discovered%20who%20wrote%20the%20letter.%20Black%20Females%20Anonymous%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20Insider's%20requests%20for%20interviews.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EAn%20uncertain%20legacy%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20letter%20was%20published%2C%20nothing%20much%20changed%2C%2010%20sources%20who%20still%20worked%20at%20Essence%20in%202020%20and%20onwards%20told%20Insider.%20In%20September%202020%2C%20mere%20months%20after%20the%20fallout%20around%20the%20letter%2C%2080%25%20of%20the%20company%20was%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.essence.com%2Fbusiness%2Fstatement-essence-covid-19-economic-impact-furlough%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efurloughed%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20according%20to%20estimates%20from%20sources%20with%20knowledge%20of%20the%20matter.%20The%20company%20went%20from%20a%20staff%20of%20around%2070%20to%20around%20nine%2C%20according%20to%20source%20estimates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20journalists%20who%20remained%20at%20the%20magazine%20were%20asked%20to%20cover%20beats%20outside%20the%20areas%20they'd%20been%20hired%20to%20report%20on.%20Some%20had%20to%20handle%20social%20media%20%E2%80%94%20outside%20their%20purview%20as%20reporters%20and%20editors%20%E2%80%94%20since%20the%20entire%20social%20media%20team%20had%20been%20furloughed%2C%20according%20to%20former%20employees.%20Essence%20staffers%20who%20survived%20the%20furloughs%20had%20to%20reach%20out%20to%20their%20ex-colleagues%20to%20ask%20for%20a%20crash%20course%20in%20social%20media%20distribution%2C%20a%20former%20employee%20said.%20The%20small%20staff%20was%20burdened%20with%20keeping%20the%20legacy%20publication%20afloat.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20company%20has%20since%20restaffed%20a%20portion%20of%20its%20workforce%2C%20a%20current%20employee%20and%20four%20employees%20who%20left%20within%20the%20past%20year%20told%20Insider%20that%20issues%20with%20work%20culture%20still%20remain.%20Staff%20who%20left%20recently%20said%20reporters%20and%20editors%20are%20still%20asked%20to%20take%20on%20additional%20responsibilities%20outside%20their%20job%20descriptions.%20A%20current%20employee%20described%20an%20environment%20that%20felt%20siloed%20and%20drained%20of%20any%20sense%20of%20community%2C%20leaving%20some%20staff%20feeling%20%26quot%3Bunappreciated%20and%20left%20out.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDennis'%20ambitions%20in%20media%2C%20as%20illustrated%20through%20his%20recent%20bids%20to%20buy%20Vice%20Media%20and%20BET%2C%20make%20some%20former%20Essence%20employees%20uneasy.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20terrifying%20prospect%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20former%20employee%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224334%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Travis%20Montaque%20and%20Richelieu%20Dennis%20speak%20during%20the%20Embracing%20the%20Influence%3A%20Black%20Culture%2C%20Media%20and%20Democracy%20panel%20at%20Inkwell%20Beach%20on%20June%2022%2C%202023%20in%20Cannes%2C%20France.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64a8301a6d7e02001af873fa%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223250%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ETravis%20Montaque%20and%20Richelieu%20Dennis%2C%20cofounders%20of%20Group%20Black%2C%20speak%20during%20the%20Embracing%20the%20Influence%3A%20Blac