20interview%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DulVqY1oADLY%26amp%3Bab_channel%3DCNBCTelevision%5C%22%3ECNBC%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20Lee%20reiterated%20his%20view%20that%20the%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fstock-market-outlook-fundstrat-price-target-increase-sp500-artificial-intelligence-2023-7%5C%22%3Ecould%20hit%20a%20new%20all-time-high%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20end%20the%20year%20at%204%2C825%2C%20implying%20an%208%25%20increase%20from%20current%20levels.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20largely%20due%20to%20cooling%20prices%20in%20the%20economy%2C%20Lee%20said%2C%20pointing%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-is-inflation-looking-consumer-price-index-june-data-2023-7%23%3A~%3Atext%3DCore%2520CPI%2520edged%2520up%2520by%2Cmonth%2520from%2520March%2520to%2520May.%5C%22%3EJune%20Consumer%20Price%20Index%20report%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Headline%20inflation%20eased%20to%203%25%20and%20core%20inflation%20eased%20to%204.8%25%2C%20in%20line%20with%20Lee's%20estimate%20for%20the%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20has%20three%20big%20tailwinds%20boosting%20it%20on%20the%20path%20to%20new%20record%20highs%2C%20Lee%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3E1.%20Inflation%20keeps%20cooling%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20results%20seen%20in%20the%20June%20CPI%20report%20are%20%26quot%3Blikely%20repeatable%2C%26quot%3B%20Lee%20said%2C%20predicting%20a%200.2%25%20price%20drop%20in%20the%20July%20and%20August%20core%20inflation%20measures.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3E2.%20The%20Fed%20pulls%20back%20on%20interest%20rate%20hikes%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EFed%20officials%20have%20raised%20interest%20rates%20from%20zero%20to%20more%20than%205%25%20in%20the%20last%20year%20to%20lower%20inflation%2C%20a%20move%20that%20weighed%20heavily%20on%20stocks%20in%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20crumbling%20inflation%20gives%20the%20central%20bank%20leeway%20to%20pause%20further%20hikes%20or%20even%20cut%20interest%20rates%2C%20Lee%20suggested%2C%20especially%20considering%20the%20drop%20in%20core%20inflation%2C%20which%20shows%20that%20inflationary%20pressures%20in%20the%20economy%20are%20receding.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3E3.%20The%20US%20avoids%20a%20recession%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3ECommentators%20have%20been%20warning%20of%20a%20recession%20for%20the%20last%20year%20as%20high%20rates%20threatened%20to%20push%20the%20economy%20into%20a%20downturn.%20But%20businesses%20have%20been%20careful%20to%20protect%20their%20profits%2C%20which%20has%20lowered%20the%20odds%20of%20recession%2C%20Lee%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20if%20a%20recession%20is%20not%20imminent%2C%20then%20I%20think%20a%20lot%20of%20folks%20are%20offsides%20and%20I%20think%20that's%20what%20propels%20markets%20to%20all%20time%20highs%2C%26quot%3B%20Lee%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20that%20the%20Fed%20can%20actually%20breathe%20a%20little%20easier%20because%20the%20economy%20hasn't%20been%20destroyed%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20later%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELee%20predicted%20the%20Fed%20would%20hike%20rates%20another%2025%20basis-points%20in%20July%20to%20assert%20its%20credibility%20on%20lowering%20inflation%2C%20which%20could%20possibly%20be%20followed%20by%20another%20rate%20hike%20in%20September.%20That%20will%20weigh%20on%20stocks%20less%20than%20the%20Fed's%20interest%20rate%20moves%20did%20last%20year%2C%20he%20said%2C%20as%20markets%20only%20have%20another%2025%20or%2050%20basis-points%20of%20tightening%20to%20go.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20lot%20less%20damage%20to%20the%20system%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BEither%20way%E2%80%A6%20we%20can%20still%20see%20earnings%20grow%20and%20get%20to%20all-time-highs.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELee%20has%20been%20among%20the%20most%20bullish%20voices%20on%20Wall%20Street%2C%20as%20other%20commentators%20warn%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22htt