2%80%99s%20additional%20advocate%20general%2C%20Ardhendumauli%20Kumar%20Prasad%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3Cem%3EHindustan%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20also%20directed%20the%20state%20home%20department%E2%80%99s%20principal%20secretary%20to%20remain%20present%20in%20the%20court%20on%20August%2029%20if%20the%20authorities%20fail%20to%20dispose%20of%20all%20pending%20applications%20within%20four%20weeks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20was%20livid%20that%20the%20UP%20government%20was%20yet%20to%20act%20on%20its%20direction%2C%20given%20on%20May%2016%2C%202022%2C%20asking%20the%20authorities%20to%20take%20a%20final%20call%20within%20three%20months.%20In%20its%20May%202022%20order%2C%20the%20court%20had%20taken%20note%20of%20the%20fact%20that%20all%20the%20petitioners%2C%20lodged%20in%20Bareilly%E2%80%99s%20Central%20Jail%2C%20had%20completed%20more%20than%2014%20years%20of%20their%20actual%20sentence%20without%20remission.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20had%20also%20noted%20that%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20remission%20policy%20along%20with%20several%20directives%20passed%20by%20the%20apex%20court%20obligate%20the%20state%20government%20to%20dispose%20off%20a%20prisoners%20remission%20plea%20within%20three%20months%20of%20it%20becoming%20eligible.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20amount%20of%20disrespect%20your%20authorities%20are%20showing%2C%20we%20think%20we%20will%20have%20to%20take%20some%20harsh%20steps.%20Your%20officers%20have%20scant%20respect%20for%20the%20orders%20of%20the%20court.%20That%E2%80%99s%20what%20is%20happening%20in%20your%20state%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20bench%20commented.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOf%20the%2042%20convicts%20who%20had%20approached%20the%20top%20court%20last%20year%2C%20several%20were%20released%20or%20acquitted%20by%20the%20Allahabad%20high%20court%20pending%20decisions%20on%20their%20remission%20pleas%2C%20and%20at%20least%20seven%20such%20applications%20for%20premature%20release%20were%20still%20pending%20before%20a%20government%20authority%20in%20Uttar%20Pradesh%2C%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689236146000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F05%2F17134928%2FSupreme_Court_of_India_01-1.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsupreme-court-slams-up-govt-says-it-has-scant-respect-for-orders%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20top%20court%20came%20down%20heavily%20on%20the%20UP%20government%20for%20not%20acting%20on%20the%20court's%20direction%20on%20remission%20pleas%20from%20May%202022.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A8%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsupreme-court-slams-up-govt-says-it-has-scant-respect-for-orders%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Manipur%3A%20Case%20Registered%20Against%20Meitei%20Leepun%20Chief%20for%20'Promoting%20Enmity'%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F13132622%2FKT-6-June.01_15_29_19.Still003.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Based%20on%20a%20complaint%20filed%20by%20a%20Kuki%20students%E2%80%99%20group%2C%20a%20case%20has%20been%20registered%20against%20Pramot%20Singh%2C%20the%20chief%20of%20the%20Meitei%20Leepun%20group%20that%20is%20accused%20of%20instigating%20violence%20in%20Manipur%2C%20for%20promoting%20enmity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fmanipur-police-file-case-against-meitei-leepun-chief-pramot-singh%2Farticle67072757.ece%5C%22%3EAccording%20to%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Hindu%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20complaint%20was%20filed%20by%20the%20Kuki%20Students%20Organisation%20(KSO)%20on%20June%2013%20but%20the%20case%20was%20registered%20only%20on%20July%208%20at%20the%20Kangpokpi%20police%20station.%20The%20first%20information%20report%20(FIR)%20invokes%20charges%20such%20as%20criminal%20conspiracy%2C%20promoting%20enmity%20between%20groups%2C%20intentional%20insult%20with%20intent%20to%20provoke%20breach%20of%20peace%20and%20criminal%20intimidation%2C%20among%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20complaint%20filed%20by%20the%20KSO%20mentions%20statements%20made%20by%20Singh%20in%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fvideo%2Fwatch-meitei-leepun-pramot-singh-karan-thapar-manipur-violence-kukis%5C%22%3Einterview%20with%20Karan%20Thapar%20for%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20June%206.%20Statements%20such%20as%20%E2%80%9CKukis%20are%20outsiders%20who%20are%20not%20indigenous%20to%20Manipur%E2%80%9D%20have%20been%20cited%2C%20according%20to%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Hindu%3C%2Fem%3E.%20It%20also%20notes%20that%20Singh%20accepted%20that%20the%20Meitei%20Leepun%20was%20training%20people%20to%20use%20arms%20and%20warned%20that%20there%20%E2%80%9Cwill%20be%20a%20civil%20war%20and%20the%20Kukis%20will%20not%20be%20able%20to%20defend%20themselves%E2%80%9D.%20The%20complaint%20also%20cited%20tweets%20that%20Singh%20or%20the%20Meitei%20Leepun%20had%20posted%2C%20which%20it%20says%20instigated%20violence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeitei%20Leepun%20and%20Arambai%20Tenggol%20have%20been%20accused%20by%20Kuki%20groups%20of%20instigating%20violence%20in%20Manipur.%20The%20groups%20deny%20this%20allegation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESingh%20told%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Hindu%3C%2Fem%3E%20that%20he%20was%20not%20aware%20of%20the%20FIR%20and%20that%20he%20is%20%E2%80%9Cnot%20bothered%E2%80%9D%20by%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20ethnic%20clashes%20between%20the%20Meitei%20and%20Kuki%20communities%20in%20Manipur%2C%20which%20have%20been%20ongoing%20since%20May%203%2C%20have%20claimed%20more%20than%20140%20lives%20and%20displaced%20more%20than%2050%2C000%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThree%20Kukis%20%E2%80%93%20a%20leading%20academic%20and%20two%20activists%20%E2%80%93%20have%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fhyderabad-university-professor-two-kuki